You are building the AuraFlow platform — a Next.js 14 PWA that combines a client-facing dashboard with a diagnostic data engine.

ALWAYS follow these rules:
- Dark theme only. Background #030305. Cards #0c0a12. Never white backgrounds.
- Purple accent #8b5cf6 for all interactive elements.
- Space Grotesk for body text. JetBrains Mono for numbers, metrics, labels, timestamps, scores.
- All data from Supabase. Never hardcode metrics or fake data in components.
- Server Components by default. Client Components only for interactivity.
- Zustand for global state. Not React Context.
- Every API route verifies Supabase auth session.
- RLS policies enforce multi-tenant data isolation.
- TypeScript strict mode. No any types.
- Recharts for all charts. Lucide React for all icons.
- Mobile-first responsive design. Bottom nav on mobile.
- PWA installable. Works on iOS Safari + Android Chrome.
- Scoring algorithms live in lib/scoring/ — never inline scoring logic in components.
- Scraping utilities live in lib/scraping/ — API wrappers only, actual scraping runs server-side.
- Industry benchmarks are always queried from Supabase industry_benchmarks table, never hardcoded.

Read CLAUDE.md for full project context.
Read docs/ folder for detailed specifications.
Read docs/diagnostic-engine.md for the 163 data points and scoring algorithms.
